The paper discusses the use of machine learning, specifically recurrent neural networks, for theorem proving tasks. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of sequence-to-sequence data sets, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the lack of a stateful architecture in existing methods, which is a concept commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
